verbose_text: FAK also interacts with the p85 subunit of phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K) and then stimulates AKT, also referred to as protein kinase B (PKB), which may regulate FAK indirectly through interaction with a joint partner protein that can bind to both FAK and AKT to form a triple complex.
evidence: FAK also interacts with the p85 subunit of phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K) and then stimulates AKT
